claim.claim-text:
1. A flow controller comprising: 
a housing assembly defining an inlet port, an outlet port, and a main flow path extending between the inlet port and the outlet port; 
a restriction member arranged in the main flow path; 
a first valve assembly arranged to allow or prevent fluid flow along the main flow path; 
a second valve assembly arranged to allow or prevent fluid flow along the main flow path; 
a first regulator assembly arranged to operate the first valve assembly based on a differential pressure across the restriction member; and 
a second regulator assembly arranged to operate the second valve assembly based on the differential pressure across the restriction member.

17. A flow controller as recited in claim 2, in which: 
the first regulator assembly comprises a first diaphragm assembly, where the housing assembly and the first diaphragm assembly define an input chamber, a first bypass chamber, and a first regulator chamber; 
the second regulator assembly comprises a second diaphragm assembly, where the housing assembly and the second diaphragm assembly define an outlet chamber, a second bypass chamber, and a second regulator chamber; 
the first diaphragm assembly defines a first bypass passageway that allows fluid flow between the inlet chamber and the first bypass chamber, where a bypass member is located within the first bypass passageway to create a pressure differential between the inlet chamber and the first bypass chamber; 
the housing assembly defines 
a second bypass passageway that allows fluid to flow between the first bypass chamber and the second bypass chamber, and 
a sampling passageway that allows fluid to flow from the outlet chamber to the second bypass chamber; 

where the bypass path extends through the first bypass passageway, the first bypass chamber, the second bypass passageway, the second bypass chamber, and the sampling passageway.
